In this task, I created and updated my profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle to start building my digital portfolio.
Before doing this, I didn’t really think much about having a professional presence online, but this task made me realize how important it is for students.
Each platform has a different purpose. 
GitHub is useful for storing and sharing projects.
LinkedIn helps in building connections and showing professional details.
Kaggle is good for practicing skills and learning new concepts.
Setting up the accounts was easy, but writing proper and professional information required some effort.
Creating the GitHub README was one of the most interesting parts because it felt like introducing myself in a short and meaningful way.
Initially, I was confused about what to include, but after seeing some examples, I got a better idea.
I plan to keep updating these profiles regularly by adding projects, achievements, and skills. 
This task helped me understand that building a digital identity is a gradual process and needs consistency.
